.container
    .jumbotron.subhead
        %h1
            = @page_title = "Modules"
            %p.lead Game Settings
    %section
        .row
            = partial('modules_sidebar')
            .col-sm-9
                .page-header
                    %h1= @page_sub_title = "Potion Effects"
                :markdown
                    To give players potion effects use the `<potion>` module in a kit and apply it to players when they spawn or enter a region.
                    Potion effects will be applied directly to the player. Duration specifies how long the potion will last in seconds and
                    amplifier determines what level / how strong the potion is. The potion type can be specified using either
                    [Minecraft effect names](http://minecraft.gamepedia.com/Data_values#Status_effects) or
                    [Bukkit potion names](/reference/potion_effects).

                    To give a custom potion item to the player use the [items](/modules/items#potions) element and its `potions` attribute.

                %h5 Potion Element
                .table-responsive
                    %table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
                        %thead
                            %tr
                                %th Element
                                %th Description
                                %th Value
                        %tbody
                            %tr
                                %td
                                    %pre
                                        %code= html_escape('<potion> </potion>')
                                %td
                                    :markdown
                                        [Minecraft effect name](http://minecraft.gamepedia.com/Data_values#Status_effects) or
                                        [Bukkit potion name](/reference/potion_effects)
                                %td
                                    %a{:href => "/reference/potion_effects"} Effect
                %h5 Potion Element
                .table-responsive
                    %table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
                        %thead
                            %tr
                                %th Attribute
                                %th Description
                                %th Value
                                %th Default
                        %tbody
                            %tr
                                %td
                                    %code duration
                                %td
                                    Duration of the effect.
                                %td
                                    %a{:href => "/reference/time_periods"} Time Period
                                %td
                                    oo
                                    (forever)
                            %tr
                                %td
                                    %code amplifier
                                %td
                                    Strength of the effect. The value matches what is displayed to the player in-game,
                                    so the first tier of potions have amplifier 1.
                                %td
                                    %span.label.label-primary Number
                                %td 1
                %h5 Example
                :markdown
                        <potion duration="10" amplifier="4">damage resistance</potion>
                        <potion duration="900" amplifier="1">jump_boost</potion>
